{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-06",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_06_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "06 - Pig and Pepper",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.729,
  "page_num": 4,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 740.384,
  "page_end_sec": 858.16,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 740.384,
      "end": 741.22,
      "text": "You'll see me there,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 741.54,
      "end": 742.44,
      "text": "said the cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 742.48,
      "end": 742.96,
      "text": "and vanished."
    },
    {
      "start": 744.384,
      "end": 746.16,
      "text": "Alice was not much surprised at this.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 746.56,
      "end": 748.58,
      "text": "she was getting so used to queer things happening,"
    },
    {
      "start": 748.92,
      "end": 751.08,
      "text": "while she was looking at the place where it had"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.08,
      "end": 751.32,
      "text": "been,"
    },
    {
      "start": 751.5,
      "end": 752.62,
      "text": "it suddenly appeared again."
    },
    {
      "start": 754.6,
      "end": 755.04,
      "text": "\"By-the-bye,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 755.22,
      "end": 756.86,
      "text": "what became of the baby?"
    },
    {
      "start": 757.14,
      "end": 757.82,
      "text": "said the cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 757.98,
      "end": 758.56,
      "text": "I'd nearly"
    },
    {
      "start": 758.7,
      "end": 759.7,
      "text": "forgotten to ask."
    },
    {
      "start": 760.78,
      "end": 761.74,
      "text": "It turned into a pig,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 761.96,
      "end": 762.96,
      "text": "Alice quietly said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 763.08,
      "end": 764.52,
      "text": "just as if it had come back in a"
    },
    {
      "start": 764.6,
      "end": 765.06,
      "text": "natural way."
    },
    {
      "start": 766.04,
      "end": 766.68,
      "text": "I thought it would,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 766.92,
      "end": 767.44,
      "text": "said the cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 767.58,
      "end": 768.26,
      "text": "and vanished again."
    },
    {
      "start": 770.048,
      "end": 770.92,
      "text": "Alice waited a little,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 771.04,
      "end": 771.28,
      "text": "half"
    },
    {
      "start": 771.36,
      "end": 772.52,
      "text": "expecting to see it again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 772.68,
      "end": 773.58,
      "text": "but it did not appear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 774.06,
      "end": 776.16,
      "text": "and after a minute or two she walked on in the"
    },
    {
      "start": 776.28,
      "end": 778.44,
      "text": "direction in which the March Hare was said to live."
    },
    {
      "start": 779.392,
      "end": 780.34,
      "text": "\"I've seen hatters before,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 780.64,
      "end": 781.26,
      "text": "she said to herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 781.48,
      "end": 783.37,
      "text": "The March Hare will be much the most interesting,"
    },
    {
      "start": 783.56,
      "end": 785.0,
      "text": "and perhaps as this is May,"
    },
    {
      "start": 785.28,
      "end": 786.52,
      "text": "it won't be raving mad,"
    },
    {
      "start": 786.88,
      "end": 789.16,
      "text": "at least not so mad as it was in March."
    },
    {
      "start": 789.98,
      "end": 790.76,
      "text": "As she said this,"
    },
    {
      "start": 790.78,
      "end": 791.36,
      "text": "she looked up,"
    },
    {
      "start": 791.56,
      "end": 792.32,
      "text": "and there was the cat"
    },
    {
      "start": 792.44,
      "end": 794.0,
      "text": "again sitting on the branch of a tree."
    },
    {
      "start": 795.26,
      "end": 797.38,
      "text": "Did you say pig or fig?",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 797.82,
      "end": 798.62,
      "text": "said the cat."
    },
    {
      "start": 799.66,
      "end": 800.4,
      "text": "I said pig,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 800.64,
      "end": 801.38,
      "text": "replied Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 801.5,
      "end": 804.28,
      "text": "and I wish you wouldn't keep appearing and vanishing so suddenly."
    },
    {
      "start": 804.74,
      "end": 806.08,
      "text": "You make one quite giddy."
    },
    {
      "start": 807.24,
      "end": 807.64,
      "text": "All right,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 807.82,
      "end": 808.6,
      "text": "said the cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 808.72,
      "end": 810.64,
      "text": "and this time it vanished quite slowly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 811.0,
      "end": 813.94,
      "text": "beginning with the end of the tail and ending with the grin,"
    },
    {
      "start": 814.08,
      "end": 816.64,
      "text": "which remained some time after the rest of it had gone."
    },
    {
      "start": 817.6,
      "end": 818.0,
      "text": "Well,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 818.12,
      "end": 819.82,
      "text": "I've often seen a cat without a grin,"
    },
    {
      "start": 819.98,
      "end": 820.6,
      "text": "thought Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 821.06,
      "end": 822.18,
      "text": "but a grin without a cat,"
    },
    {
      "start": 822.32,
      "end": 825.08,
      "text": "it's the most curious thing I ever saw in all my life."
    },
    {
      "start": 825.94,
      "end": 827.86,
      "text": "She had not gone much farther before she",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 827.86,
      "end": 829.74,
      "text": "came in sight of the house of the March Hare."
    },
    {
      "start": 830.54,
      "end": 831.96,
      "text": "She thought it must be the right house,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 832.08,
      "end": 833.84,
      "text": "because the chimneys were shaped like ears,"
    },
    {
      "start": 834.46,
      "end": 835.82,
      "text": "and the roof was thatched with fur."
    },
    {
      "start": 836.06,
      "end": 838.94,
      "text": "It was so large a house that she did not like to go nearer"
    },
    {
      "start": 839.0,
      "end": 841.64,
      "text": "till she had nibbled some more of the left-hand bit of mushroom,"
    },
    {
      "start": 841.82,
      "end": 843.54,
      "text": "and raised herself to about two"
    },
    {
      "start": 843.54,
      "end": 844.0,
      "text": "feet high."
    },
    {
      "start": 844.3,
      "end": 847.29,
      "text": "Even then she walked up towards it rather timidly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 847.3,
      "end": 848.02,
      "text": "saying to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 849.12,
      "end": 850.98,
      "text": "\"Suppose it should be raving mad after all!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 851.44,
      "end": 853.77,
      "text": "I almost wish I'd gone to see the Hatter instead!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 857.22,
      "end": 858.16,
      "text": "End of chapter 6",
      "para_break": true
    }
  ]
}